{"word":"H3807 - כָּתַת - kâthath - kaw-thath' - Beat","slug":"H3807","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">כָּתַת</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>kâthath"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kaw-thath'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Beat"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DB;&#x05BC;&#x05EA;&#x05EA; - ka&#x0302;thath</b> - <i>kaw-thath'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>bruise</i> or violently <i>strike: - </i>beat (down, to pieces), break in pieces, crushed, destroy, discomfit, smite, stamp."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3795\">H3795</a>, <a href=\"#/H4386\">H4386</a>"}]}